post_text: With summer in full force and temperatures reaching 111¬∞ this weekend, staying hydrated is important for both physical and mental health. While the amount of water needed daily varies from person to person, an 8oz glass of water 8 times a day is a good place to start! A great way to up your water intake when you don‚Äôt particularly like water is by eating food with a high water content such as watermelon, cucumber, or grapefruit. You can also add fruit to your water for a flavor and vitamin boost. Tag your friends to remind them to drink their water!

CHS Families Pantry Pickup & Go

Knowing that many of our families rely on school meals for their children, we will be offering Pickup & Go Pantry items to be picked up in the CHS parking lot from 10am to 12pm starting Monday, March 23rd and throughout the week until Friday March 27th. Items may include dry beans, rice, chips and other pantry items.

Families do not need to register for meals and there will be no income requirements.

Please observe social distancing guidelines while picking up items. While supplies last.

post_text:
Compass High School is an innovative charter school in Tucson, Arizona that provides teenagers with a choice from the conventional public education system. We cater to all different learning styles & we encourage students to self-advocate & express their identity through their learning. Our goal as educators is to give students the resources they need to challenge themselves, become passionate about life-long learning, & become active, capable citizens.

Learn more at compasshighschool.com
